Sentencas: Binary nanocomposite thin films of lanthanum strontium cobaltite and gadolinia-doped ceria (La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta, LSC-GDC) were prepared using pulsed laser deposition (PLD) for application as cathodes of low-temperature operating solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC).
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The thin films were fabricated under identical deposition conditions, but the LSC:GDC mixing ratio was varied.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The PLD-processed LSC-GDC nanocomposites exhibit different physical and electrochemical properties than do conventional powder-processed composite SOFC cathodes.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The LSC:GDC mixing ratio not only alters the composition of the LSC-GDC nanocomposite thin films but also affects their crystallographic orientation and microstructure.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The major component of the composite appears to govern the physical properties of the LSC-GDC nanocomposite thin films.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties measured with AC impedance spectroscopy during the half-cell tests reveal that the electrochemical performance of the LSC-GDC nanocomposite cathode is enhanced as the LSC content in the composite increases, which is in contrast to the behavior of powder-processed composite cathodes.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio

Sentencas: The present study provides important insight, into the design and application of thin-film-processed nanocomposite electrodes.
Titulo: Physical and Electrochemical Characteristics of Pulsed Laser Deposited La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-δ-Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ Nanocomposites as a Function of the Mixing Ratio
